-27T22:07:45Z","due_on":null,"closed_at":null},"comments":0,"created_at":"2021-03-25T00:29:55Z","updated_at":"2021-10-19T15:49:26Z","closed_at":"2021-10-19T15:49:26Z","author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"We need to remove the `IntegrationCLITestCase` and `AsyncExitStackTestCase`\nclasses and merge them into the `AsyncTestCase` class.\n\nThe main issue here will be `self._stack` and `self._astack` which might be used\nin other testcases.\n\n`AsyncExitStackTestCase.setUp()` currenly creates them.\n\n```python\n        self._stack = contextlib.ExitStack().__enter__()\n        self._astack = await contextlib.AsyncExitStack().__aenter__()\n```\n\nWe need to find the test cases that might be issues. We're guessing that the\nbiggest issue with be needing to add the `super().setUp()` call in each test\ncase that overrides `setUp()`.\n\nAlso, there may be some that create temporary directories on `setUpClass()` and\nthis might confuse them.\n\nThe recommened way to go about this it to merge the test cases classes into\n`AsyncTestCase`, see what fails, and go from there.\n\n## References\n\n- [`dffml/util/asynctestcase.py`](https://github.com/intel/dffml/blob/master/dffml/util/asynctestcase.py)\n\n- `$ git grep -E 'IntegrationCLITestCase|AsyncExitStackTestCase|AsyncTestCase'`\n","closed_by":{"login":"pdxjohnny","id":5950433,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU5NTA0MzM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5950433?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/pdxjohnny","html_url":"https://github.com/pdxjohnny","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pdxjohnny/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pdxjohnny/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pdxjohnny/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pdxjohnny/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pdxjohnny/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pdxjohnny/or